  "body": "### Description\n\nIdToken is generated internally when OIDC is used to connect to GitHub and other OAuth2 providers.\r\n\r\nIt is generated and signed with `quarkus-smallrye-jwt-build` with a default lifespan set to 5 mins. So after 5 mins this token is invalidated and requires a new redirect to authenticate again.\r\n\r\nThis lifespan can be currently controlled with a `smallrye.jwt.new-token.lifespan` property, but it is a global property which will affect the lifetime for all generated tokens, not only internal ID tokens, so may not work in all cases. Therefore it would be better to have a property to control the internal ID token lifespan in the `quarkus.oidc.` namespace\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
